{{Infobox artwork | image_file = PAN sculpture.jpg | painting_alignment = Front | image_size = 300 px | title = Pan | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = Roger White (sculptor) | year = {{Start date|1980}} | type = [[Bronze]], limestone | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = 30 | width_imperial = 14 | length_imperial = 19 | metric_unit = cm | imperial_unit = in | city = [[Indianapolis]], [[Indiana]], [[United States]] | museum = | coordinates = {{coord|39|46|19|N|86|9|27|W|region:US}} | owner = City of Indianapolis }}
'''''Pan''''' is a public artwork by sculptor [[Roger White (sculptor)|Roger White]] located at the [[Indiana World War Memorial Plaza]] in [[Indianapolis, Indiana]], [[United States]]. This work was originally surveyed in 1993 as part of the [[Smithsonian Institution|Smithsonian's]] [[Save Outdoor Sculpture!]] program. A former water fountain, this piece is part of a [[National Historic Landmark District]].<ref name="SOS">{{cite web | author=Save Outdoor Sculpture | year=1993 | title=Syrinx (sculpture). | work=SOS | publisher=Smithsonian | url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!314194~!0#focus | accessdate= 6 January 2010}}</ref>
==Description== [[File:Pan Label.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Plaque]] It is a [[bronze]] figure of [[Pan (god)|Pan]] sitting on a [[limestone]] tree stump. Pan is [[Nude (art)|nude]] and his furry proper right knee is bent upwards to his chest with his other leg hangs over the side of the stump. The [[satyr]] holds a [[pan flute]] in his hand, holding it up to his mouth, as if playing it for nearby [[Syrinx (sculpture)|''Syrinx'']].<ref name="SOS"/>
==Information==
''Pan'' was originally designed by [[Myra Reynolds Richards]]. Richards' original ''Syrinx'' and ''Pan'' sculptures were dedicated in 1923. Eventually, both pieces were stolen, with ''Syrinx'' disappearing in 1959 and ''Pan'' c. 1970. The parks department commissioned [[Adolph Wolter]] to replace the pieces, and in 1973 they were reinstalled in their current location in University Park at the [[Indiana World War Memorial Plaza]]. However, Wolter's ''Pan'' would eventually be stolen as well, and sculptor Roger White was commissioned to replace the piece. ''Pan'' was replaced in 1980 by White.<ref name="SOS"/>
